    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-11-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-11-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="267" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d267">
                <head>No. 267.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Lowell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-11-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 30,
                            1883</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 716.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose herewith for your information a copy
                        of a dispatch from Mr. Heap, chargé d’affaires at Constantinople<note n="*" xml:id="d267fn1">See Mr. Heap to Mr. Frelinghuysen, No. 296, October 31,
                            1883, <hi rend="italic">post.</hi>
                    </note> from which it appears <pb facs="0549" n="479" xml:id="pg_479"/> that Lord Dufferin, at Mr. Heap’s
                        request, has instructed Colonel Everett, Her Britannic Majesty’s consul at
                        Erzeroum, to give the American missionaries in that vicinity all the
                        assistance they may desire.</p>
                <p>I will thank you to convey to the British Government an expression of the
                        President’s high appreciation of Lord Dufferin’s courtesy in aiding our
                        minister in the protection of American citizens.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
